1
00:00:14,781 --> 00:00:17,517
A strange dance...

2
00:00:24,557 --> 00:00:27,293
A strange dance...

3
00:00:37,103 --> 00:00:39,072
A strange...

4
00:00:40,140 --> 00:00:44,310
dance...
I guess...

5
00:01:22,849 --> 00:01:26,219
I recall the image of a bird
spreading its wings.

6
00:01:26,453 --> 00:01:29,856
The bird looks at its reflection
in a puddle.

7
00:01:30,156 --> 00:01:33,359
Wet with water, its feathers
gleam faintly.

8
00:01:33,460 --> 00:01:36,696
Perhaps it flew through trees
laden with morning dew.

9
00:01:36,796 --> 00:01:39,232
Even before the sun had fully risen,

10
00:01:39,332 --> 00:01:41,601
its rays shone upon the bird's wings,

11
00:01:41,701 --> 00:01:44,104
making them glisten so beautifully.

12
00:01:44,404 --> 00:01:47,507
The bird in the puddle shakes its body,

13
00:01:47,607 --> 00:01:51,111
and I can clearly see every drop
that is shaken off.

14
00:01:51,211 --> 00:01:55,215
That's right. It's so crystal clear.

15
00:01:55,715 --> 00:01:59,319
Many such sights exist in my mind.

16
00:01:59,419 --> 00:02:02,755
I could say that I paint pictures

17
00:02:03,156 --> 00:02:06,392
to download what's in my head.

18
00:02:06,493 --> 00:02:09,629
There's a strange reality
in the panoramas of my mind.

19
00:02:09,729 --> 00:02:14,267
And the resulting pictures
are just landscapes, so to speak.

20
00:02:14,467 --> 00:02:17,804
Up until now, they haven't sold so well.

21
00:02:21,474 --> 00:02:23,176
It was sunny outside.

22
00:02:23,276 --> 00:02:25,712
I grabbed an empty paint tube
from the desk

23
00:02:25,812 --> 00:02:28,414
and threw it in the bin,
dust scattering.

24
00:02:28,515 --> 00:02:32,152
Caught in the spring sunlight
streaming through the window,

25
00:02:32,252 --> 00:02:35,655
the particles sparkled,
as they swirled and danced.

26
00:02:36,589 --> 00:02:39,392
Despite the beautiful weather,
my mood is dark.

27
00:02:39,492 --> 00:02:43,463
Over the past few weeks, I've struggled
to paint anything meaningful.

28
00:02:43,563 --> 00:02:46,332
It's not that I can't.

29
00:02:46,432 --> 00:02:48,801
I just don't have the motivation.

30
00:02:49,302 --> 00:02:52,639
I find myself alternating between
my bed and the canvas.

31
00:02:52,772 --> 00:02:54,207
It's frustrating.

32
00:03:02,182 --> 00:03:03,249
Birds.

33
00:03:03,349 --> 00:03:07,620
(Bird chirping)

34
00:03:07,854 --> 00:03:09,289
I envy birds.

35
00:03:09,389 --> 00:03:11,724
They always seem to be having fun,

36
00:03:11,824 --> 00:03:15,195
and have a reason to live
without even working.

37
00:03:15,795 --> 00:03:16,863
See.

38
00:03:16,963 --> 00:03:22,368
(Sound of bird song and flapping wings)

39
00:03:29,442 --> 00:03:31,244
It's time to play that piece.

40
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:46,960
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

41
00:03:47,260 --> 00:03:48,995
(Cat meowing)

42
00:03:57,837 --> 00:04:13,519
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

43
00:04:13,519 --> 00:04:25,832
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)
」Moon and Cat Dance」

44
00:04:25,832 --> 00:04:29,002
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

45
00:04:30,470 --> 00:04:35,475
｢Bremen｣
♪～

46
00:04:35,475 --> 00:05:35,501
♪～

47
00:05:35,601 --> 00:05:38,004
♪Hey, no need to think.

48
00:05:38,104 --> 00:05:40,773
♪We can't understand each other with empty talk.

49
00:05:40,873 --> 00:05:43,042
♪Let‘s just ride this sound for now.

50
00:05:43,343 --> 00:05:46,045
♪I want to keep it in my heart.

51
00:05:46,346 --> 00:05:48,348
♪Our bodies are achromatic, laid back.

52
00:05:48,448 --> 00:05:50,783
♪Just grooving with the swelling sound of rain.

53
00:05:50,883 --> 00:05:53,353
♪Shall we live together forever

54
00:05:53,453 --> 00:05:58,424
♪in a corner of this night?

55
00:05:58,524 --> 00:06:15,808
♪～

56
00:06:15,908 --> 00:06:18,611
♪Hey, we can be good-for-nothing.

57
00:06:18,711 --> 00:06:21,447
♪It was you who said so and asked me out.

58
00:06:21,547 --> 00:06:23,616
♪It's not fun when you're just logical.

59
00:06:23,716 --> 00:06:26,552
♪Do you still hate to waste your time?

60
00:06:26,652 --> 00:06:28,621
♪Vacuum-packing the scenery of us parading.

61
00:06:28,721 --> 00:06:31,657
♪Grooving with the sound of stomping feet.

62
00:06:31,758 --> 00:06:33,693
♪As if we were the town musicians of Bremen,

63
00:06:33,793 --> 00:06:36,662
♪we march on, just the two of us.

64
00:06:36,763 --> 00:06:42,668
♪Now, inhale and exhale real quick.

65
00:06:46,406 --> 00:06:49,041
♪Singing is the best we can do.

66
00:06:49,142 --> 00:06:51,911
♪How about laughing, why not join me?

67
00:06:52,011 --> 00:06:54,414
♪I'm singing a song of love.

68
00:06:54,514 --> 00:06:56,182
♪Ha haha.

69
00:06:56,516 --> 00:06:59,085
♪Taking it easy is the best we can do.

70
00:06:59,185 --> 00:07:01,821
♪Nothing in this world is worth dying for.

71
00:07:01,921 --> 00:07:03,923
♪What shall we do tomorrow?

72
00:07:04,190 --> 00:07:06,959
♪If you have time, let's understand each other.

73
00:07:07,059 --> 00:07:26,712
♪～

74
00:07:26,813 --> 00:07:29,449
♪Hey, no need to think.

75
00:07:29,549 --> 00:07:31,984
♪Your cells have started dancing.

76
00:07:32,084 --> 00:07:34,220
♪Let's just ride this sound for now.

77
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:37,023
♪It's okay if you can't.

78
00:07:37,123 --> 00:07:39,492
♪Backpacking in the scenery of memories.

79
00:07:39,592 --> 00:07:41,928
♪Grooving with the murmur of the spring wind.

80
00:07:42,028 --> 00:07:44,730
♪Let's keep on singing together.

81
00:07:44,831 --> 00:07:47,099
♪If you have time, why don't we do some loving?

82
00:07:47,533 --> 00:07:53,673
♪Now, inhale and do it aloud.

83
00:07:57,109 --> 00:07:59,812
♪Singing is the best we can do.

84
00:07:59,912 --> 00:08:02,582
♪I can't complain about being laughed at.

85
00:08:02,682 --> 00:08:04,984
♪Everything is just wrong. See?

86
00:08:05,084 --> 00:08:06,986
♪Ha haha.

87
00:08:07,086 --> 00:08:09,956
♪Taking it easy is the best we can do.

88
00:08:10,056 --> 00:08:12,658
♪It's not easy to pretend to be a fool.

89
00:08:12,758 --> 00:08:17,763
♪The lyrics are almost the same,
so you can skip the third verse.

90
00:08:17,864 --> 00:08:27,807
♪～

91
00:08:27,907 --> 00:08:34,013
♪Now, inhale and exhale real quick.

92
00:08:37,950 --> 00:08:43,723
♪Hey, let me have your heart, just for today.

93
00:08:48,127 --> 00:08:51,664
♪Singing is the best we can do. Am I wrong?

94
00:08:51,764 --> 00:08:55,635
♪Are you all laughing at me? Say it.

95
00:08:57,737 --> 00:09:00,540
♪Taking it easy is the best we can do.

96
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:03,075
♪Let's run away if life is killing you.

97
00:09:03,175 --> 00:09:08,047
♪In a few years, nobody would remember anything.

98
00:09:08,314 --> 00:09:10,650
♪Let's keep singing while wheezing.

99
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:13,252
♪Can you move? Why not join me?

100
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:15,888
♪I'm singing a song of love.

101
00:09:15,988 --> 00:09:17,857
♪Ha haha.

102
00:09:17,957 --> 00:09:20,760
♪Taking it easy is the best we can do.

103
00:09:20,860 --> 00:09:23,262
♪Nothing in this world is worth dying for.

104
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:25,665
♪What shall we do tomorrow?

105
00:09:25,765 --> 00:09:28,234
♪If you have time, let's laugh together

106
00:09:28,334 --> 00:09:30,703
♪and understand each other in the meantime.

107
00:09:30,803 --> 00:10:37,870
♪～

108
00:10:38,671 --> 00:10:43,676
｢Rain with Cappuccino｣
♪～

109
00:10:43,676 --> 00:10:58,024
♪～

110
00:10:58,124 --> 00:11:01,293
♪Words that turned grayish white

111
00:11:01,394 --> 00:11:05,665
♪remind me of the color of cappuccino.

112
00:11:07,967 --> 00:11:12,772
♪No excuses. Leave them by the window.

113
00:11:16,108 --> 00:11:17,743
♪There are just too many.

114
00:11:17,843 --> 00:11:36,395
♪～

115
00:11:36,696 --> 00:11:39,832
♪Hearts that turned grayish white

116
00:11:39,932 --> 00:11:43,803
♪remind me of the color of cappuccino.

117
00:11:46,172 --> 00:11:51,277
♪No excuses. Let's gulp down the cappuccino,

118
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:53,245
♪pretending to be just joking.

119
00:11:54,780 --> 00:11:59,085
♪Now the rain flows as if wavering.

120
00:11:59,185 --> 00:12:04,056
♪Drowning in the flowers that bring us a storm,

121
00:12:04,156 --> 00:12:09,028
♪I wish for a memory that never lets you fade away.

122
00:12:09,128 --> 00:12:13,065
♪Please, please,

123
00:12:13,866 --> 00:12:18,070
♪please, so that you wouldn't overflow.

124
00:12:18,170 --> 00:12:36,388
♪～

125
00:12:36,489 --> 00:12:41,160
♪I wait for the waves at the coast as the setting sun

126
00:12:41,894 --> 00:12:44,029
♪reflects red light on the window.

127
00:12:46,198 --> 00:12:49,368
♪August in Visby, the roaring sea.

128
00:12:49,468 --> 00:12:53,806
♪I wait in vain. A sea breeze is all I have.

129
00:12:54,774 --> 00:13:00,880
♪Whiteness of the flowers that swam through summer,
the evening rain.

130
00:13:00,980 --> 00:13:03,883
♪Drowning in the night that flows by,

131
00:13:03,983 --> 00:13:08,554
♪I wish for a flower that never lets anyone fade away.

132
00:13:09,021 --> 00:13:12,925
♪Please, please,

133
00:13:13,893 --> 00:13:18,230
♪please, place it inside of my heart.

134
00:13:18,330 --> 00:13:35,881
♪～

135
00:13:35,981 --> 00:13:37,917
♪Something has been wrong with me.

136
00:13:38,017 --> 00:13:40,519
♪I want you to tell me just one way to live,

137
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:44,256
♪but Ino longer have anything to give in return.

138
00:13:45,524 --> 00:13:49,929
♪If you have no answer, just one word will do.

139
00:13:50,029 --> 00:13:51,463
♪I don't get it.

140
00:13:51,564 --> 00:13:54,400
♪I really don't get it.

141
00:13:59,505 --> 00:14:03,909
♪Now the rain flows as if wavering.

142
00:14:04,009 --> 00:14:08,547
♪Drowning in the flowers that bring us a storm,

143
00:14:08,848 --> 00:14:13,619
♪I write songs so that you wouldn't fade away.

144
00:14:13,919 --> 00:14:17,857
♪Please, please,

145
00:14:18,524 --> 00:14:22,528
♪please, let them stay in my memory.

146
00:14:22,628 --> 00:14:25,030
♪Another summer has passed,

147
00:14:25,130 --> 00:14:27,233
♪with a flower held in my heart.

148
00:14:27,333 --> 00:14:30,269
♪Behind my teary eyelids,

149
00:14:30,369 --> 00:14:36,575
♪I hold this song so that you wouldn't fade away.

150
00:14:37,910 --> 00:14:40,079
♪Please,

151
00:14:40,212 --> 00:14:44,350
♪please, so that you wouldn't overflow.

152
00:14:44,450 --> 00:15:07,406
♪～

153
00:15:36,502 --> 00:15:38,637
(Sigh)

154
00:15:54,553 --> 00:15:58,123
Something is lacking in your paintings.

155
00:15:58,223 --> 00:16:00,192
That's what she said that day.

156
00:16:00,559 --> 00:16:04,596
My ex-girlfriend who broke up with me
and left this place.

157
00:16:04,697 --> 00:16:09,201
She's a promoter who works mostly on
small exhibitions in the city.

158
00:16:09,301 --> 00:16:11,670
According to her, she said,

159
00:16:11,971 --> 00:16:14,273
」Your pictures look like photos.」

160
00:16:14,506 --> 00:16:17,710
Not because they are drawn precisely.

161
00:16:18,010 --> 00:16:21,747
But because they are like copies of
scenery that can be found anywhere.

162
00:16:23,549 --> 00:16:25,584
They're just... not interesting.

163
00:16:27,553 --> 00:16:29,154
Her eyes were right.

164
00:16:29,254 --> 00:16:32,992
People aren't touched by pictures drawn
without any thought.

165
00:16:33,092 --> 00:16:37,129
Truth is, I've been content
being an unsuccessful artist,

166
00:16:37,229 --> 00:16:39,665
barely ever drawing pictures.

167
00:16:45,337 --> 00:16:47,272
Night has come.

168
00:16:47,606 --> 00:16:52,311
Ultimately, I was never inspired
and spent the day aimlessly.

169
00:16:52,611 --> 00:16:55,147
Maybe I need a change of scenery.

170
00:16:55,247 --> 00:16:58,550
(Wind)

171
00:16:59,151 --> 00:17:02,788
When I open the window,
a warm breeze blows in.

172
00:17:04,223 --> 00:17:07,026
The moonlight shines down
between the clouds.

173
00:17:07,126 --> 00:17:09,261
It sneaks inside through the window

174
00:17:09,361 --> 00:17:12,364
and dances off the piano keys like a fish.

175
00:17:13,232 --> 00:17:16,035
There's a perfect song for this feeling.

176
00:17:16,135 --> 00:17:20,305
It's a piano sonata
that even an amateur like me can play.

177
00:17:26,545 --> 00:17:34,586
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

178
00:17:34,686 --> 00:17:44,363
(Bird chirping)
(Wings fluttering)

179
00:17:45,697 --> 00:17:47,266
A bird.

180
00:17:52,371 --> 00:17:53,405
Hey.

181
00:17:55,441 --> 00:17:56,542
Go on.

182
00:17:57,643 --> 00:17:59,645
What's wrong. Go.

183
00:18:04,349 --> 00:18:06,351
It was a small canary.

184
00:18:06,452 --> 00:18:11,390
It stares at me with tiny,
black, beady eyes.

185
00:18:11,490 --> 00:18:15,327
Its beak is round and pointed,
like a peanut.

186
00:18:15,427 --> 00:18:21,667
It stands, its feet sticking out of its yellow
feathers, grasping the window sill.

187
00:18:22,801 --> 00:18:23,769
Go on.

188
00:18:26,605 --> 00:18:30,342
Oh well. Whatever. A tiny spectator.

189
00:18:30,709 --> 00:18:31,710
Ah...

190
00:18:32,277 --> 00:18:34,880
I always sit at the piano the same way.

191
00:18:35,180 --> 00:18:36,515
I put my hands on the keys.

192
00:18:36,615 --> 00:18:38,650
I check the position of the notes.

193
00:18:38,750 --> 00:18:40,586
I place my foot on the pedals.

194
00:18:40,686 --> 00:18:42,855
I sit up straight and raise my face.

195
00:18:43,155 --> 00:18:45,824
Then I tense my arms.

196
00:18:48,193 --> 00:18:54,800
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

197
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:57,402
(Wings fluttering)

198
00:19:06,278 --> 00:19:07,513
(Clears throat)

199
00:19:10,315 --> 00:19:12,551
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

200
00:19:12,551 --> 00:19:17,723
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)
(Wings fluttering)

201
00:19:17,723 --> 00:19:17,823
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

202
00:19:17,823 --> 00:19:20,492
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)
The canary spreads its wings.

203
00:19:20,492 --> 00:19:21,226
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

204
00:19:21,226 --> 00:19:25,197
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)
It opens them slowly,
goes off balance, then closes them.

205
00:19:25,197 --> 00:19:25,931
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

206
00:19:32,371 --> 00:19:34,606
I try playing a single long note.

207
00:19:34,706 --> 00:19:36,942
(Piano plays)
(Sound of flapping wings)

208
00:19:37,242 --> 00:19:39,411
It spreads its wings wide.

209
00:19:39,878 --> 00:19:42,514
This time, I play a note, short and quick.

210
00:19:42,614 --> 00:19:43,549
(Piano plays)

211
00:19:43,649 --> 00:19:45,551
(Wings fluttering)

212
00:19:45,851 --> 00:19:49,855
It flaps its wings then quickly stops.

213
00:19:52,224 --> 00:19:54,326
I blink my eyes.

214
00:19:54,693 --> 00:19:57,863
Have I finally lost my mind?

215
00:19:59,831 --> 00:20:05,370
The canary stares at me
with its beady, black eyes.

216
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:24,523
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

217
00:20:24,623 --> 00:20:28,994
The canary spreads its yellow wings wide.

218
00:20:29,595 --> 00:20:33,865
With the moonlight shining on it,
it glows faintly.

219
00:20:33,966 --> 00:20:36,535
It flutters its wings,

220
00:20:37,302 --> 00:20:41,540
as if it is dancing a waltz
to my poor piano playing.

221
00:20:43,909 --> 00:20:44,943
Hah...

222
00:20:45,344 --> 00:20:47,346
I smile without thinking.

223
00:20:47,579 --> 00:20:48,480
On a whim,

224
00:20:48,580 --> 00:20:52,317
I grab the sketchbook
and pencil from the music stand.

225
00:20:52,417 --> 00:20:54,786
The canary stands there without moving.

226
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:59,858
I think, 」This is the first time
I've drawn a living canary.」

227
00:21:00,425 --> 00:21:01,893
The night draws on.

228
00:21:17,509 --> 00:21:18,577
Even the next day,

229
00:21:18,677 --> 00:21:21,446
I sit before the canvas
scratching my head.

230
00:21:21,546 --> 00:21:24,483
As always,
I don't feel as if I can draw a thing.

231
00:21:24,583 --> 00:21:27,786
But I think I drew
an interesting sketch yesterday.

232
00:21:27,919 --> 00:21:30,422
Well, it's just a drawing of a canary.

233
00:21:30,522 --> 00:21:32,991
I don't think I can use it for anything.

234
00:21:33,525 --> 00:21:36,395
I stand up and stretch.

235
00:21:37,596 --> 00:21:39,431
Then, I thought about

236
00:21:39,531 --> 00:21:43,035
the canary who flew off
somewhere after last night.

237
00:21:43,902 --> 00:21:47,306
I open the window and look
at the sea far away.
(Sound of the sea breeze)

238
00:21:47,306 --> 00:21:47,572
(Sound of the sea breeze)

239
00:21:47,572 --> 00:21:49,708
(Sound of the sea breeze)
The sea breeze is blowing.

240
00:21:49,708 --> 00:21:50,976
(Sound of the sea breeze)

241
00:21:50,976 --> 00:21:55,847
(Sound of the sea breeze)
I imagine the yellow wings that have flown

242
00:21:55,847 --> 00:21:56,615
(Sound of the sea breeze)

243
00:21:56,615 --> 00:21:58,817
(Sound of the sea breeze)
so very far away.

244
00:21:58,817 --> 00:22:00,085
(Sound of the sea breeze)

245
00:22:03,422 --> 00:22:08,427
｢Goodbye Molten｣
♪～

246
00:22:08,427 --> 00:22:24,676
♪～

247
00:22:24,776 --> 00:22:27,779
♪With the book I borrowed in one hand,

248
00:22:27,879 --> 00:22:31,783
♪I walk along the sidewalk by the river.

249
00:22:32,050 --> 00:22:35,354
♪Two more pages and I'll get to the ending.

250
00:22:35,454 --> 00:22:39,124
♪I don't want to know what lies ahead.

251
00:22:40,125 --> 00:22:54,039
♪～

252
00:22:54,139 --> 00:22:57,442
♪A boy riding on a goose's back

253
00:22:57,542 --> 00:23:01,613
♪flies on and on toward the north.

254
00:23:01,713 --> 00:23:04,683
♪His buddy is a goose named Molten.

255
00:23:04,783 --> 00:23:08,553
♪That's the novel I'm reading.

256
00:23:10,422 --> 00:23:13,658
♪Goodbye, Molten.

257
00:23:13,759 --> 00:23:17,729
♪We used to try and see if we could fly.

258
00:23:17,829 --> 00:23:21,900
♪We opened our arms and jumped high,

259
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:24,970
♪knowing that nothing would happen.

260
00:23:25,103 --> 00:23:28,407
♪Goodbye, Molten.

261
00:23:28,507 --> 00:23:32,544
♪You laughed as you rolled over.

262
00:23:32,644 --> 00:23:36,648
♪Catching a faint smell of earth,

263
00:23:36,748 --> 00:23:40,152
♪I almost got choked up inside.

264
00:23:41,620 --> 00:23:43,722
♪Summer was already there.

265
00:23:43,822 --> 00:23:56,902
♪～

266
00:23:57,002 --> 00:24:00,439
♪With sadness as an asset,

267
00:24:00,539 --> 00:24:04,142
♪I walk along the street in early summer.

268
00:24:04,443 --> 00:24:07,612
♪Two more pages and I'll get to the ending.

269
00:24:07,712 --> 00:24:11,650
♪I don't want to know what lies ahead yet.

270
00:24:11,750 --> 00:24:14,853
♪Chasing you who got slightly taller,

271
00:24:14,953 --> 00:24:18,924
♪I would run toward our favorite hill.

272
00:24:19,057 --> 00:24:22,461
♪Just like a goose flying in the sky,

273
00:24:22,561 --> 00:24:26,598
♪we would open up our arms.

274
00:24:27,833 --> 00:24:30,936
♪Good bye, Molten.

275
00:24:31,036 --> 00:24:35,173
♪We still tried to see if we could fly

276
00:24:35,474 --> 00:24:42,547
♪just because we didn't want to know
that we were not special.

277
00:24:42,747 --> 00:24:45,750
♪Goodbye, Molten.

278
00:24:45,851 --> 00:24:50,055
♪You laughed as you rolled over,

279
00:24:50,155 --> 00:24:54,059
♪looking like you had no idea

280
00:24:54,159 --> 00:24:57,496
♪that we were growing up.

281
00:24:57,596 --> 00:24:59,931
♪Summer was already there.

282
00:25:00,031 --> 00:25:12,577
♪～

283
00:25:12,677 --> 00:25:16,047
♪You'd grow even taller.

284
00:25:16,248 --> 00:25:19,784
♪Someday you'd be far away.

285
00:25:19,951 --> 00:25:23,555
♪We'd get separated little by little

286
00:25:23,755 --> 00:25:27,158
♪like growing branches.

287
00:25:27,259 --> 00:25:30,929
♪With the faded book in one hand,

288
00:25:31,029 --> 00:25:34,666
♪I walk along the street I used to know.

289
00:25:34,799 --> 00:25:38,203
♪From that hill, I'm a few hundred steps away.

290
00:25:38,603 --> 00:25:41,273
♪I see someone standing there.

291
00:25:45,277 --> 00:25:48,613
♪Goodbye, Molten.

292
00:25:48,713 --> 00:25:52,717
♪I notice you were still trying to fly

293
00:25:52,817 --> 00:25:55,086
♪with bright eyes,

294
00:25:55,186 --> 00:26:00,125
♪just like the way you used to be.

295
00:26:00,225 --> 00:26:03,194
♪Goodbye, Molten.

296
00:26:03,295 --> 00:26:09,935
♪I think I know now, because we can't fly,
we're precious all the more.

297
00:26:10,035 --> 00:26:14,839
♪A faint smell, I almost get choked up inside.

298
00:26:14,940 --> 00:26:17,275
♪You've been watching me

299
00:26:17,576 --> 00:26:22,747
♪with a smile that had never faded.

300
00:26:24,182 --> 00:26:26,184
♪Summer is already here.

301
00:26:26,284 --> 00:26:39,297
♪～

302
00:26:39,598 --> 00:26:42,601
♪With the faded book in one hand,

303
00:26:42,701 --> 00:26:46,605
♪I walk along the sidewalk by the river.

304
00:26:46,838 --> 00:26:49,908
♪One more page and I'll get to the ending.

305
00:26:50,008 --> 00:26:53,678
♪Now I turn the last page.

306
00:26:53,778 --> 00:26:56,247
♪Goodbye, Molten.

307
00:27:06,324 --> 00:27:11,329
｢Matasaburo｣
♪～

308
00:27:11,329 --> 00:27:25,877
♪～

309
00:27:26,177 --> 00:27:29,114
♪Stepping into a puddle,

310
00:27:31,082 --> 00:27:35,086
♪you give a big yawn.

311
00:27:35,987 --> 00:27:38,690
♪I want you to bring a terrible storm,

312
00:27:39,224 --> 00:27:43,261
♪strong enough to blow this sky away.

313
00:27:45,330 --> 00:27:47,732
♪I've been waiting for the wind

314
00:27:47,832 --> 00:27:53,271
♪because monotonous life must be such a bore.

315
00:27:55,006 --> 00:27:57,175
♪I've been waiting for the wind.

316
00:27:57,275 --> 00:27:59,844
♪I've been waiting for the wind.

317
00:28:03,915 --> 00:28:07,719
♪Let it blow hard through green leaves.

318
00:28:07,886 --> 00:28:12,323
♪Blow off everything, even words.

319
00:28:12,424 --> 00:28:17,228
♪And leave everyone speechless

320
00:28:17,328 --> 00:28:20,765
♪by swallowing and carrying us all away.

321
00:28:20,865 --> 00:28:27,472
♪Doddo-do, dodoh-do

322
00:28:27,772 --> 00:28:40,452
♪～

323
00:28:40,752 --> 00:28:43,388
♪So, is it true that you bring a storm?

324
00:28:45,290 --> 00:28:49,427
♪As I asked with my eyes wide open,

325
00:28:50,228 --> 00:28:53,098
♪you said to me bluntly,

326
00:28:53,498 --> 00:28:57,736
♪」The world is my oyster.」

327
00:28:59,871 --> 00:29:02,240
♪I've been waiting for the wind

328
00:29:02,340 --> 00:29:08,113
♪because the society I fit in is way too uncomfortable.

329
00:29:09,247 --> 00:29:11,483
♪」Then let it rain even harder!

330
00:29:11,783 --> 00:29:14,385
♪Let the wind blow this feeling away.」

331
00:29:18,189 --> 00:29:21,960
♪Let it blow hard through green leaves.

332
00:29:22,127 --> 00:29:26,965
♪Throw away anything and everything.

333
00:29:27,065 --> 00:29:31,469
♪If we remain this way,

334
00:29:31,836 --> 00:29:36,441
♪we'll soon forget even who we are.

335
00:29:36,541 --> 00:29:40,879
♪Blow off the green walnuts.

336
00:29:41,045 --> 00:29:45,850
♪Blow off the sour quinces.

337
00:29:46,117 --> 00:29:50,989
♪Blow harder, terribly harder.

338
00:29:51,089 --> 00:29:55,560
♪Bring the wind to destroy this city.

339
00:29:56,828 --> 00:30:00,431
♪Blow, blow hard through green leaves.

340
00:30:00,532 --> 00:30:05,303
♪Throw away anything and everything.

341
00:30:05,403 --> 00:30:11,910
♪Our sadness, our dreams, blow everything away,

342
00:30:12,010 --> 00:30:15,146
♪Matasaburo

343
00:30:16,014 --> 00:30:19,417
♪It's a long road ahead.

344
00:30:19,851 --> 00:30:24,556
♪Now I see words are your wind.

345
00:30:24,856 --> 00:30:29,260
♪Just leave everyone speechless

346
00:30:29,360 --> 00:30:32,597
♪by swallowing and carrying us all away.

347
00:30:32,897 --> 00:30:39,571
♪Doddo-do, dodoh-do

348
00:30:39,871 --> 00:30:52,917
♪～

349
00:31:05,096 --> 00:31:09,267
A single deer stares at me.

350
00:31:11,202 --> 00:31:16,307
I stand beneath a tree with red blossoms.

351
00:31:18,042 --> 00:31:21,079
I am holding a small box.

352
00:31:23,047 --> 00:31:28,586
I realize that this is a dream.

353
00:31:34,893 --> 00:31:37,295
(Sigh)

354
00:31:42,300 --> 00:31:46,004
I think it's like my girlfriend
once said long ago.

355
00:31:46,204 --> 00:31:48,339
My pictures are not interesting.

356
00:31:48,439 --> 00:31:50,408
They lack any kind of appeal.

357
00:31:50,508 --> 00:31:53,611
In creative work,
the message alone isn't everything.

358
00:31:53,912 --> 00:31:57,348
If you want a picture to sell,
it needs to tell a story.

359
00:31:57,448 --> 00:31:59,083
Unless your picture

360
00:31:59,183 --> 00:32:01,953
has something that says, 」Look at me,」

361
00:32:02,053 --> 00:32:04,656
it will never touch other people's hearts.

362
00:32:04,989 --> 00:32:07,959
As a child, I was better at art
than with people.

363
00:32:08,059 --> 00:32:11,529
Come to think of it, I still want to draw
what I wanted to then.

364
00:32:11,996 --> 00:32:15,633
I have a very clear picture
of a scene in my mind.

365
00:32:15,934 --> 00:32:19,370
Whenever I want to draw,
that comes to mind first.

366
00:32:19,704 --> 00:32:23,641
A road where sunlight shines
between the trees.

367
00:32:23,942 --> 00:32:25,977
A shopping arcade at sunset.

368
00:32:26,077 --> 00:32:27,578
A bench and a church.

369
00:32:27,946 --> 00:32:30,014
A town in a foreign country.

370
00:32:30,448 --> 00:32:32,717
Rain on a cafe terrace.

371
00:32:33,985 --> 00:32:36,387
It's so clear, it's annoying.

372
00:32:37,188 --> 00:32:41,059
I can even see clearly each leaf
in an unfamiliar landscape.

373
00:32:41,159 --> 00:32:45,163
I output it onto the canvas
without making a single change to it.

374
00:32:46,130 --> 00:32:50,702
My drawings are not interesting.

375
00:32:53,671 --> 00:32:57,041
My drawings are not interesting.

376
00:32:59,644 --> 00:33:01,746
(Sigh)

377
00:33:02,413 --> 00:33:05,183
Another day has ended.

378
00:33:05,650 --> 00:33:07,285
I light a cigarette

379
00:33:07,385 --> 00:33:10,488
and place my hands on
the window sill as I exhale.

380
00:33:10,588 --> 00:33:14,359
Then I feel something slimy
on my fingertips.

381
00:33:14,525 --> 00:33:15,693
Yuck.

382
00:33:17,362 --> 00:33:19,998
I see something light green.

383
00:33:20,098 --> 00:33:24,002
(Frog croaking)

384
00:33:24,102 --> 00:33:25,603
It's a frog.

385
00:33:26,371 --> 00:33:29,474
I don't like these kinds of things.

386
00:33:30,541 --> 00:33:34,512
Hey. Go away. Get out.

387
00:33:34,746 --> 00:33:38,016
Don't make me say,
」Leap frog out of here.」

388
00:33:38,116 --> 00:33:39,717
Hurry up. Get out.

389
00:33:40,752 --> 00:33:45,556
I have a strange sense of
déjà vu as I shoo it away.

390
00:33:45,656 --> 00:33:49,060
I feel as if I did
something similar before.

391
00:33:50,561 --> 00:33:52,196
Oh well. Whatever.

392
00:34:11,382 --> 00:34:13,117
Whoa!

393
00:34:13,217 --> 00:34:15,086
(Frog croaking)

394
00:34:15,486 --> 00:34:17,622
The thing came inside.

395
00:34:18,122 --> 00:34:20,258
Give me a break, would you?

396
00:34:20,591 --> 00:34:24,195
Hey, this isn't your home, you know.

397
00:34:24,295 --> 00:34:25,596
Go on. Get out.

398
00:34:25,696 --> 00:34:26,697
(Clicks tongue)

399
00:34:29,500 --> 00:34:32,570
I finally realize why I feel this déjà vu.

400
00:34:33,104 --> 00:34:36,441
It's that canary that showed up one day.

401
00:34:36,541 --> 00:34:39,744
This thing has
that same strange impudence.

402
00:34:40,511 --> 00:34:43,414
I give up and drop my arms,
striking the piano keys.

403
00:34:43,514 --> 00:34:45,216
(Piano sound)

404
00:34:45,650 --> 00:34:48,853
The frog twitches.

405
00:34:50,788 --> 00:34:54,725
I tentatively raise my index finger
and press a key again.

406
00:34:54,826 --> 00:34:56,260
It's a G note.

407
00:34:56,360 --> 00:34:58,729
(Piano plays)

408
00:34:59,730 --> 00:35:02,834
The frog slowly lifts its body.

409
00:35:03,134 --> 00:35:06,104
I play the key again, and the frog moves.

410
00:35:07,271 --> 00:35:09,607
I pull out the chair and sit down again.

411
00:35:09,707 --> 00:35:13,377
Then I play the melody from 」Moonlight.」

412
00:35:15,713 --> 00:35:24,122
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

413
00:35:24,222 --> 00:35:28,559
With its body still lifted,
it raises its arms.

414
00:35:29,193 --> 00:35:30,394
On a whim,

415
00:35:30,495 --> 00:35:32,864
I grab the sketchbook and pencil again.

416
00:35:33,164 --> 00:35:36,767
I sketch the figure of the still frog
with its head held high

417
00:35:36,868 --> 00:35:38,569
with my pen.

418
00:35:39,370 --> 00:35:41,372
Though it's an ordinary frog,

419
00:35:41,472 --> 00:35:44,876
it's almost as if
it has a mysterious allure to it.

420
00:35:45,176 --> 00:35:48,446
I draw, and then I play the piano again.

421
00:35:48,546 --> 00:35:51,282
I draw and play, play and draw.

422
00:35:51,415 --> 00:35:54,418
It's figure is now in my sketchbook.

423
00:35:55,486 --> 00:35:59,657
The frog's arms slowly wander in the air,

424
00:36:00,224 --> 00:36:02,793
as if it is looking for something.

425
00:36:03,828 --> 00:36:06,564
I can smell the night sea breeze.

426
00:36:07,565 --> 00:36:10,401
The frog lifts its nose high

427
00:36:10,501 --> 00:36:13,938
and flaps it little green arms.

428
00:36:14,539 --> 00:36:19,677
It looked as if it was dancing
a strange dance.

429
00:36:23,447 --> 00:36:28,319
｢Howl At The Moon｣
♪～

430
00:36:28,319 --> 00:36:40,665
♪～

431
00:36:40,831 --> 00:36:43,868
♪Howling at the moon by the roadside,

432
00:36:43,968 --> 00:36:46,971
♪a shadow walks through the town.

433
00:36:48,906 --> 00:36:51,876
♪Not knowing what it's like to be full,

434
00:36:51,976 --> 00:36:54,845
♪the night slips into the depth.

435
00:36:56,881 --> 00:36:59,850
♪I find myself in a crowd of people,

436
00:36:59,951 --> 00:37:03,254
♪all are staring at my face.

437
00:37:04,855 --> 00:37:07,825
♪What do you know about me?

438
00:37:07,925 --> 00:37:10,995
♪I ask them pretending to be a beast.

439
00:37:13,664 --> 00:37:17,668
♪I want to throw out the whole thing.

440
00:37:17,768 --> 00:37:21,439
♪I want you to tell me that I'm alive.

441
00:37:21,539 --> 00:37:25,843
♪Sing like howling at the moon, ah,

442
00:37:25,943 --> 00:37:27,712
♪how brilliant.

443
00:37:29,880 --> 00:37:33,818
♪I want to crush the earth with an ice pick

444
00:37:33,918 --> 00:37:37,555
♪and fill it with my malice.

445
00:37:37,655 --> 00:37:41,492
♪Sing like howling at the moon,

446
00:37:41,592 --> 00:37:47,732
♪ah, and you can be selfish, act as you wish.

447
00:37:47,832 --> 00:38:02,780
♪～

448
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:05,783
♪The pale moon by the roadside.

449
00:38:05,883 --> 00:38:09,487
♪」Where is it?」 I hear people say.

450
00:38:10,888 --> 00:38:13,791
♪I wonder if anyone can see

451
00:38:13,891 --> 00:38:17,061
♪this ugly beast.

452
00:38:18,896 --> 00:38:21,799
♪Turn towards the direction they point at.

453
00:38:21,899 --> 00:38:24,902
♪Keep moving without a face.

454
00:38:26,904 --> 00:38:29,807
♪Something is staring at me

455
00:38:29,907 --> 00:38:33,311
♪from that shadow of the harbor.

456
00:38:35,680 --> 00:38:39,583
♪I don't believe in the whole thing.

457
00:38:39,684 --> 00:38:43,554
♪Nobody expects anything from you.

458
00:38:43,654 --> 00:38:47,825
♪Sing like howling at the moon, ah,

459
00:38:47,925 --> 00:38:49,860
♪how brilliant.

460
00:38:51,962 --> 00:38:59,403
♪I want to dip a hard pen in the moon
reflected on a lake to draw a line on the waves.

461
00:38:59,503 --> 00:39:03,808
♪Sing like howling at the moon, ah,

462
00:39:03,908 --> 00:39:06,010
♪how glamorous.

463
00:39:06,110 --> 00:39:10,014
♪Go with the flow of time.

464
00:39:10,915 --> 00:39:24,628
♪～

465
00:39:24,729 --> 00:39:33,738
♪Everyone thinks I'm a poor sick guy,

466
00:39:34,672 --> 00:39:37,475
♪I know that!

467
00:39:38,576 --> 00:39:45,683
♪～

468
00:39:45,783 --> 00:39:49,553
♪I want to throw out the whole thing.

469
00:39:49,687 --> 00:39:53,424
♪No, I'm not done with violating the world.

470
00:39:53,524 --> 00:39:57,461
♪Sing like howling at the moon,

471
00:39:57,561 --> 00:40:00,064
♪ah, how brilliant.

472
00:40:01,932 --> 00:40:05,836
♪I want you to crush my skull with an ice pick

473
00:40:05,936 --> 00:40:09,440
♪and fill it with lukewarm soup.

474
00:40:09,540 --> 00:40:13,444
♪Sing like howling at the moon,

475
00:40:13,577 --> 00:40:20,084
♪ah, you, a beast in the back of my throat,

476
00:40:21,919 --> 00:40:27,925
♪and this world will be all yours.

477
00:40:28,025 --> 00:40:42,807
♪～

478
00:40:42,907 --> 00:40:46,010
♪Howl at the moon by the roadside.

479
00:40:53,017 --> 00:40:58,022
｢451｣
♪～

480
00:40:58,022 --> 00:41:14,672
♪～

481
00:41:14,772 --> 00:41:17,541
♪Looking at that sun

482
00:41:18,008 --> 00:41:19,677
♪burning so deeply,

483
00:41:19,777 --> 00:41:25,049
♪I notice a small fire around my chest.

484
00:41:25,149 --> 00:41:30,254
♪Then a passerby says out loud,

485
00:41:30,554 --> 00:41:35,960
♪」Look at that weirdo,」 with a laugh.

486
00:41:36,060 --> 00:41:45,769
♪My fingertip touches a piece of paper
and finally puts it on fire.

487
00:41:45,870 --> 00:41:49,173
♪Now catch fire and burn,

488
00:41:49,273 --> 00:41:51,909
♪burn, burn,

489
00:41:52,009 --> 00:41:54,645
♪burn, burn.

490
00:41:54,745 --> 00:41:56,614
♪Love the joy.

491
00:41:56,714 --> 00:41:59,884
♪Now sublimate and dance,

492
00:41:59,984 --> 00:42:02,686
♪dance, dance,

493
00:42:02,786 --> 00:42:07,791
♪dance, dance,

494
00:42:07,925 --> 00:42:09,894
♪dance.

495
00:42:10,060 --> 00:42:18,702
♪～

496
00:42:18,802 --> 00:42:23,741
♪There, see the faces of people gathering around

497
00:42:23,841 --> 00:42:29,013
♪looking for the intent of the flameI spread.

498
00:42:29,113 --> 00:42:31,916
♪Look at those weirdos.

499
00:42:32,016 --> 00:42:34,318
♪See how they raise their voices

500
00:42:34,618 --> 00:42:39,723
♪and lose their heads over a mere flame.

501
00:42:39,823 --> 00:42:44,995
♪Burn, make it fast, amid booming angry shouts.

502
00:42:45,095 --> 00:42:49,867
♪Let the stack of paper burn red and bright.

503
00:42:49,967 --> 00:42:52,069
♪Ah, what a bother,

504
00:42:52,169 --> 00:42:55,873
♪now burn, burn, burn,

505
00:42:55,973 --> 00:42:58,676
♪burn, burn.

506
00:42:58,776 --> 00:43:00,678
♪Love the sadness too.

507
00:43:00,778 --> 00:43:03,914
♪Now set fire and dance,

508
00:43:04,014 --> 00:43:06,317
♪dance, dance,

509
00:43:06,617 --> 00:43:11,288
♪dance, dance,

510
00:43:11,889 --> 00:43:13,824
♪dance.

511
00:43:13,924 --> 00:43:22,633
♪～

512
00:43:22,766 --> 00:43:27,972
♪Touch to put it out, touch to put it out.

513
00:43:28,072 --> 00:43:33,210
♪Touch to open my heart's window.

514
00:43:33,310 --> 00:43:38,248
♪Burn fast and show the ashes.

515
00:43:38,349 --> 00:43:43,354
♪The soul smoldering deep inside—

516
00:43:43,654 --> 00:43:46,657
♪Now make it catch fire and burn,

517
00:43:46,757 --> 00:43:49,193
♪burn, burn,

518
00:43:49,293 --> 00:43:51,862
