806
01:05:02,064 --> 01:05:02,164
(The sound of a chameleon tail
tapping the piano top)

807
01:05:02,164 --> 01:05:05,201
(The sound of a chameleon tail
tapping the piano top)
Sometimes,
the tip of its curled tail extends,

808
01:05:05,201 --> 01:05:05,301
(The sound of a chameleon tail
tapping the piano top)

809
01:05:05,301 --> 01:05:09,005
(The sound of a chameleon tail
tapping the piano top)
and its shadow traces
the black keys of the piano,

810
01:05:09,338 --> 01:05:12,909
swaying back and forth
like the surface of waves.

811
01:05:16,379 --> 01:05:19,982
I'm used to it now.
I don't care what comes anymore.

812
01:05:20,182 --> 01:05:21,918
(Tapping on window)

813
01:05:23,219 --> 01:05:26,923
One night, I hear
the sound of tapping on the window.

814
01:05:27,023 --> 01:05:29,592
It was a beautiful night
with a waning moon.

815
01:05:29,692 --> 01:05:32,061
I listen closely.

816
01:05:32,228 --> 01:05:36,632
There is also a strange sound,
like of a poorly fitted door closing.

817
01:05:36,933 --> 01:05:39,201
(Sound of something creaking)

818
01:05:48,077 --> 01:05:49,612
It's a deer.

819
01:06:08,364 --> 01:06:09,632
It's a deer.

820
01:06:09,999 --> 01:06:12,134
A stag is sitting there.

821
01:06:12,234 --> 01:06:16,005
It's a stag with horns
and a beautiful coat.

822
01:06:16,105 --> 01:06:19,175
It's lying curled up
just outside the window,

823
01:06:19,275 --> 01:06:21,510
lifting its head and looking at me.

824
01:06:21,610 --> 01:06:26,015
I catch a whiff of what I once smelled
in a cowshed on a farm.

825
01:06:26,349 --> 01:06:28,284
(Tapping on the window)

826
01:06:29,452 --> 01:06:32,555
No way. This time it's impossible.

827
01:06:32,755 --> 01:06:34,523
(Tapping on window)

828
01:06:35,291 --> 01:06:37,493
Oh, give me a break.

829
01:06:38,394 --> 01:06:41,130
I can hear the deer's breathing.

830
01:06:42,565 --> 01:06:44,000
(Sigh)

831
01:06:45,267 --> 01:06:46,702
I finally give up,

832
01:06:47,003 --> 01:06:50,239
and back away toward the piano.

833
01:06:50,339 --> 01:06:52,108
I play a single note

834
01:06:52,208 --> 01:06:54,643
and hear that creaking door sound.

835
01:06:54,744 --> 01:06:56,612
(Sound of something creaking)

836
01:06:56,712 --> 01:06:59,682
There's no doubt.
That is the sound it makes.

837
01:06:59,782 --> 01:07:04,553
As if trying to escape reality,
I am impressed by the sound it makes.

838
01:07:05,654 --> 01:07:09,058
I begin playing the introduction,
which I have played often.

839
01:07:11,327 --> 01:07:14,196
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

840
01:07:14,296 --> 01:07:16,799
(Deer's moan)

841
01:07:21,237 --> 01:07:24,573
Please, try to be silent.

842
01:07:25,474 --> 01:07:27,610
(Deer's moan)

843
01:07:29,211 --> 01:07:32,181
Try not to moan.

844
01:07:32,348 --> 01:07:33,649
(Tapping on window)

845
01:07:33,749 --> 01:07:35,351
None of that either.

846
01:07:36,485 --> 01:07:38,220
The deer watches me

847
01:07:38,320 --> 01:07:42,525
with a gaze
that's as black as the deep night,

848
01:07:43,092 --> 01:07:46,162
a mysterious color that draws you in.

849
01:07:50,766 --> 01:07:58,841
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

850
01:07:59,141 --> 01:08:01,377
The deer closes its eyes.

851
01:08:01,477 --> 01:08:05,347
Then it opens and closes
its mouth again and again.

852
01:08:05,714 --> 01:08:07,249
It raises its head

853
01:08:07,349 --> 01:08:10,386
and stretches its nose
as if to approach the window.

854
01:08:10,486 --> 01:08:14,356
Occasionally, its red tongue peeks out.

855
01:08:15,424 --> 01:08:18,194
I can hear the deer's breathing.

856
01:08:18,461 --> 01:08:21,597
For some reason,
the sound has a nostalgic feel.

857
01:08:22,431 --> 01:08:26,469
After finishing the introduction,
I start playing 」Moonlight」 again.

858
01:08:27,136 --> 01:08:32,308
The deer lowers its head back down,
opens its eyes, and looks at me.

859
01:08:34,376 --> 01:08:36,412
This is the only part I can play.

860
01:08:37,713 --> 01:08:40,116
The deer looks at me.

861
01:08:40,216 --> 01:08:42,618
It's as if he's saying, 」That's fine.」

862
01:08:43,185 --> 01:08:46,222
I start playing 」Moonlight」 again.

863
01:08:47,723 --> 01:08:51,427
I play only the introduction,

864
01:08:51,794 --> 01:08:55,164
as if going round and round
in the same place.

865
01:08:57,867 --> 01:09:47,850
(Waves)

866
01:09:48,250 --> 01:09:59,795
(Sound of a toy piano)

867
01:10:00,396 --> 01:10:03,832
(Owl hooting)

868
01:10:04,733 --> 01:10:09,805
I found this on the beach.
Some one must have tossed it out.

869
01:10:09,905 --> 01:10:12,474
It made me wonder

870
01:10:12,575 --> 01:10:15,878
if it would dance
if it wasn't played on my piano.

871
01:10:18,380 --> 01:10:20,749
I see feathers sticking out of the pot.

872
01:10:20,849 --> 01:10:25,788
I bet I'm the only human
who's ever carried an owl in a pot.

873
01:10:25,888 --> 01:10:28,724
It's dark black eyes look at me.

874
01:10:28,824 --> 01:10:33,495
There are yellow circles like egg yolks
covering those black eyes,

875
01:10:33,596 --> 01:10:35,598
like crescent moons.

876
01:10:35,965 --> 01:10:39,668
I open my sketchbook
and start drawing with my pencil.

877
01:10:39,768 --> 01:10:43,806
The owl in the pot stands there
with a puzzled look.

878
01:10:49,845 --> 01:10:54,617
Long ago, I often used to dream of
becoming a bird.

879
01:10:55,584 --> 01:10:58,587
Oh. Not a bird like you.

880
01:10:58,887 --> 01:11:01,624
A bird that spreads its wings wide.

881
01:11:02,524 --> 01:11:06,028
Its wings shining faintly with the dew

882
01:11:06,528 --> 01:11:10,466
that wet its wings
as it flew between the trees.

883
01:11:10,699 --> 01:11:15,404
The sunlight before it has fully risen is
almost annoyingly beautiful.

884
01:11:15,504 --> 01:11:17,439
My body shivers.

885
01:11:18,974 --> 01:11:21,644
Then, I fly

886
01:11:22,378 --> 01:11:24,346
toward the sun.

887
01:11:24,847 --> 01:11:28,384
Eventually, I run out of energy and fall.

888
01:11:29,585 --> 01:11:32,521
When I woke up, I remembered it clearly.

889
01:11:32,621 --> 01:11:35,324
When I drew it on paper,

890
01:11:35,557 --> 01:11:38,494
I got a mysteriously good feeling.

891
01:11:39,695 --> 01:11:44,366
Now that I think about it,
that was the first picture I drew.

892
01:11:44,833 --> 01:11:47,736
(Sound of a toy piano)

893
01:11:50,005 --> 01:11:53,909
I doubt I am any different than then.

894
01:11:54,009 --> 01:11:57,079
Or rather, I have not changed.

895
01:11:57,579 --> 01:12:00,382
I am better at using a brush and pen,

896
01:12:00,482 --> 01:12:02,318
but that is all.

897
01:12:02,418 --> 01:12:06,622
Only my sketching is better.
Only my perspective is more accurate.

898
01:12:06,722 --> 01:12:09,692
Only my lines are more beautiful.

899
01:12:11,493 --> 01:12:15,597
What is in my head, what is before me,

900
01:12:15,698 --> 01:12:18,834
I am merely copying what I see there.

901
01:12:19,001 --> 01:12:21,370
When asked if that's what I want to draw,

902
01:12:21,470 --> 01:12:23,372
I tilt my head.

903
01:12:25,607 --> 01:12:27,343
I am empty.

904
01:12:28,777 --> 01:12:30,913
I sometimes become afraid.

905
01:12:31,814 --> 01:12:34,917
Is what I am doing actually

906
01:12:36,452 --> 01:12:40,022
not much different than
what a camera does?

907
01:12:44,059 --> 01:12:48,764
(Sound of a toy piano)

908
01:12:50,532 --> 01:12:54,503
When I think too much about things
like that, I play this song.

909
01:12:54,803 --> 01:12:58,640
Piano sonata 14, the Moonlight Sonata.

910
01:12:58,874 --> 01:13:00,809
I love this song.

911
01:13:00,909 --> 01:13:03,645
I was taught it when I was a child.

912
01:13:03,746 --> 01:13:08,717
It clearly sounds like a depressing song,
but how can I put this...

913
01:13:10,652 --> 01:13:13,155
Nobody has ever agreed with me on this,

914
01:13:13,455 --> 01:13:16,625
but when I play this, I become incredibly

915
01:13:18,660 --> 01:13:20,629
nostalgic.

916
01:13:27,636 --> 01:13:29,705
My eyes meet the yellow crescent moons.

917
01:13:30,539 --> 01:13:33,542
I don't care and keep playing the keys.

918
01:13:33,976 --> 01:13:36,578
Every time the scratchy sound is played,

919
01:13:36,678 --> 01:13:41,183
I see the owl fluffing its wings
in discomfort.

