♪Setting sunbursts and it doesn't let our eyes open.

1024
01:30:33,594 --> 01:30:48,109
♪～

1025
01:30:48,209 --> 01:30:51,846
♪It's sad but it can't be helped.

1026
01:30:51,946 --> 01:30:55,716
♪My hands got wet in the sun.

1027
01:30:56,117 --> 01:30:59,487
♪Such unbearable brightness

1028
01:30:59,587 --> 01:31:03,191
♪made me feel lost on my way home.

1029
01:31:04,692 --> 01:31:10,965
♪Like falling,

1030
01:31:14,135 --> 01:31:16,103
♪the madder-colored sunlight hit me.

1031
01:31:16,204 --> 01:31:19,841
♪Just a little more

1032
01:31:19,941 --> 01:31:24,946
♪I could almost love a piece of myself.

1033
01:31:25,680 --> 01:31:31,252
♪But the setting sun didn't let my eyes open
before I knew it

1034
01:31:35,623 --> 01:31:39,260
♪in the quiet evening calm.

1035
01:31:46,267 --> 01:31:49,804
♪It's sad but it can't be helped.

1036
01:31:49,904 --> 01:31:53,708
♪My hands touched the sun.

1037
01:31:54,108 --> 01:31:57,645
♪Like burning with a feeble flame,

1038
01:31:57,745 --> 01:32:01,616
♪it scorched just my fingertips.

1039
01:32:01,883 --> 01:32:05,219
♪Like grapes hanging from a high branch,

1040
01:32:05,520 --> 01:32:09,156
♪it's unreachable, so don't you dare.

1041
01:32:09,724 --> 01:32:12,994
♪I wonder if I fell in love.

1042
01:32:13,094 --> 01:32:16,831
♪Like that setting sun,

1043
01:32:18,099 --> 01:32:25,806
♪if there's no reason for falling,

1044
01:32:27,708 --> 01:32:32,880
♪I'd rather—

1045
01:32:32,980 --> 01:32:45,259
♪～

1046
01:32:45,560 --> 01:32:52,233
♪Our cheeks glow red by soft sunlight.

1047
01:32:52,333 --> 01:33:04,612
♪Setting sun bursts and if it just lights up our way—

1048
01:33:04,712 --> 01:33:13,254
♪Then I could almost love a piece of myself.

1049
01:33:14,121 --> 01:33:19,961
♪I saw you smiling shyly at the setting sun.

1050
01:33:23,931 --> 01:33:27,702
♪In the quiet evening calm,

1051
01:33:31,872 --> 01:33:35,743
♪we can't even open our eyes.

1052
01:33:48,623 --> 01:33:53,628
｢Fireworks of Shoes｣
♪～

1053
01:33:53,628 --> 01:33:56,230
♪～

1054
01:33:56,330 --> 01:33:58,232
♪Hey, hey,

1055
01:33:58,332 --> 01:34:04,271
♪I want to say something, but I fall short of words

1056
01:34:04,372 --> 01:34:10,878
♪because I'm struck speechless.

1057
01:34:12,413 --> 01:34:13,948
♪So—

1058
01:34:14,048 --> 01:34:28,295
♪～

1059
01:34:28,396 --> 01:34:30,231
♪Hey, hey,

1060
01:34:30,331 --> 01:34:36,203
♪We remain silent, but we don't need words

1061
01:34:36,303 --> 01:34:41,075
♪because the eyes are so eloquent.

1062
01:34:43,411 --> 01:34:51,385
♪We forget things as a result of the bugs
starting to eat them.

1063
01:34:51,686 --> 01:34:59,026
♪In my memory, I see nothing but smiling faces.

1064
01:34:59,126 --> 01:35:03,164
♪In the color of dusk, we fly through the sky.

1065
01:35:03,264 --> 01:35:07,168
♪Fly on and even out of the atmosphere.

1066
01:35:07,268 --> 01:35:12,106
♪Right below, what looks smaller and smaller

1067
01:35:12,206 --> 01:35:15,142
♪is the city where you lived.

1068
01:35:15,242 --> 01:35:19,046
♪Flowers burst at the tip of my shoes.

1069
01:35:19,146 --> 01:35:23,084
♪Big flowers of fire burst into bloom.

1070
01:35:23,184 --> 01:35:29,457
♪I'll leave my whole heart here.
I thought so somehow.

1071
01:35:29,757 --> 01:35:33,494
♪I saw the summer like that.

1072
01:35:33,794 --> 01:35:48,175
♪～

1073
01:35:48,442 --> 01:35:50,277
♪Hey, hey,

1074
01:35:50,377 --> 01:35:56,117
♪I want to know you, but I can't make up my mind

1075
01:35:56,383 --> 01:36:01,122
♪because I'm sure you'll boast about it.

1076
01:36:04,425 --> 01:36:12,233
♪There's nothing to make me feel relieved,

1077
01:36:12,333 --> 01:36:17,438
♪but the sky is beautiful today as usual.

1078
01:36:19,340 --> 01:36:27,381
♪All the things I ate should be the price of my life.

1079
01:36:27,481 --> 01:36:35,089
♪It's too late for me and I can't even
be the nighthawk.

1080
01:36:35,189 --> 01:36:39,059
♪In the color of dawn, we dance in the sky.

1081
01:36:39,160 --> 01:36:43,097
♪It's nonsense to ask what to wish for.

1082
01:36:43,197 --> 01:36:46,934
♪I've grown up and forgotten.

1083
01:36:47,034 --> 01:36:51,105
♪My eyes that reflect you get in my way.

1084
01:36:51,205 --> 01:36:55,142
♪Far below, flowers boomed.

1085
01:36:55,242 --> 01:36:59,113
♪Big flowers of fire boomed.

1086
01:36:59,213 --> 01:37:05,419
♪Just hearing the sound makes me cry.
I thought so somehow.

1087
01:37:05,519 --> 01:37:10,057
♪I heard the summer like that.

1088
01:37:10,157 --> 01:37:40,287
♪～

1089
01:37:40,387 --> 01:37:42,156
♪Hey, hey,

1090
01:37:42,256 --> 01:37:48,262
♪I want to fly, but I don't know when to stop

1091
01:37:48,362 --> 01:37:55,035
♪because I know I'll look for you.

1092
01:37:56,370 --> 01:37:57,938
♪So—

1093
01:37:59,173 --> 01:38:03,077
♪In the color of dusk, we fly through the sky.

1094
01:38:03,177 --> 01:38:07,014
♪Fly on and even out of this planet's present state.

1095
01:38:07,114 --> 01:38:10,517
♪Right below, what became smaller

1096
01:38:10,618 --> 01:38:15,122
♪and vanished is the city where you lived.

1097
01:38:15,222 --> 01:38:19,226
♪Flowers burst in the summer sky.

1098
01:38:19,326 --> 01:38:23,063
♪Big flowers of fire burst into bloom.

1099
01:38:23,163 --> 01:38:29,503
♪I want to keep crying forever.
I thought so somehow.

1100
01:38:29,603 --> 01:38:34,208
♪The summer like that is gone.

1101
01:38:34,308 --> 01:38:49,623
♪～

1102
01:39:06,273 --> 01:39:10,210
Okay. I see.

1103
01:39:11,011 --> 01:39:14,581
Yes. I'll be careful.

1104
01:39:15,249 --> 01:39:17,184
Thank you always.

1105
01:39:17,384 --> 01:39:20,220
The exhibition? It's coming soon.

1106
01:39:20,321 --> 01:39:24,458
As a sign of gratitude, as my landlord,
can I invite you?

1107
01:39:24,725 --> 01:39:29,396
Oh, I see. Ha ha ha...
No, it's okay.

1108
01:39:29,496 --> 01:39:31,999
Yes. Okay.

1109
01:39:33,067 --> 01:39:34,335
Goodbye.

1110
01:39:39,506 --> 01:39:42,609
It's not easy living in this day and age.

1111
01:39:45,079 --> 01:39:47,648
Seems like I haven't painted for days.

1112
01:39:47,748 --> 01:39:50,584
Probably because I've been busy prepping.

1113
01:39:51,018 --> 01:39:52,186
(Cat meowing)

1114
01:39:52,353 --> 01:39:55,022
I hear a cat meowing somewhere.

1115
01:39:55,122 --> 01:39:57,191
I open the window and look outside.

1116
01:39:57,491 --> 01:39:59,126
Nothing there.

1117
01:39:59,226 --> 01:40:00,427
Oh well, whatever.

1118
01:40:00,527 --> 01:40:04,264
I leave the window open
and sit at the piano.

1119
01:40:05,733 --> 01:40:07,301
I touch the keys.

1120
01:40:07,401 --> 01:40:10,437
I begin playing the intro
to 」Moonlight.」

1121
01:40:11,305 --> 01:40:18,045
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

1122
01:40:19,480 --> 01:40:24,218
After playing a while,
I hear something at the window.

1123
01:40:24,551 --> 01:40:28,789
A cat suddenly appears
and sits on the piano.

1124
01:40:29,523 --> 01:40:32,559
I watch the cat as I continue playing.

1125
01:40:33,193 --> 01:40:36,730
The cat raises its nose
into the air and stands up.

1126
01:40:37,564 --> 01:40:42,202
It closes its eyes,
as if listening to the notes.

1127
01:40:43,237 --> 01:40:45,205
I stop playing.

1128
01:40:45,305 --> 01:40:47,441
The cat stops moving.

1129
01:40:48,275 --> 01:40:52,346
It opens its eyes
and I see the tips of its hair moving.

1130
01:40:57,184 --> 01:40:59,386
I've been drawing pictures of you.

1131
01:40:59,486 --> 01:41:01,722
All of these here.

1132
01:41:01,822 --> 01:41:04,525
They're pretty fun, right?

1133
01:41:05,325 --> 01:41:09,763
I guess the landlord must have seen me.

1134
01:41:10,264 --> 01:41:13,467
He said he thought I'd been feeding
the animals.

1135
01:41:13,567 --> 01:41:15,769
When I told him the animals came

1136
01:41:16,070 --> 01:41:18,539
simply because I was playing the piano,

1137
01:41:18,639 --> 01:41:21,375
he looked at me as if I was mad.

1138
01:41:22,342 --> 01:41:26,713
So he told me he's taking back
the piano at the end of the month.

1139
01:41:27,381 --> 01:41:30,317
This belongs to the landlord.

1140
01:41:30,517 --> 01:41:33,687
His niece wants to learn,
so he's giving it to her.

1141
01:41:33,787 --> 01:41:38,125
Mind you, I'm sure there were
complaints about the noise, too.

1142
01:41:39,693 --> 01:41:43,464
This piano is going to disappear.

1143
01:41:45,232 --> 01:41:50,270
That means there's no reason
for you guys to keep coming.

1144
01:41:53,207 --> 01:41:58,178
I don't like it.
You're not disposable materials.

1145
01:41:58,879 --> 01:42:01,248
It's thanks to you, I made this art,

1146
01:42:01,348 --> 01:42:04,184
and I've been able to do
a solo exhibition.

1147
01:42:04,418 --> 01:42:06,787
I mean, you guys,

1148
01:42:06,887 --> 01:42:09,223
you come here to hear me play, right?

1149
01:42:09,556 --> 01:42:22,803
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

1150
01:42:22,903 --> 01:42:26,607
The eyes of the cat sitting on
the piano meet mine.

1151
01:42:28,208 --> 01:42:30,277
I'm stunned.

1152
01:42:31,879 --> 01:42:36,483
The cats' eyes are
the color of the deep night.

1153
01:42:38,552 --> 01:42:43,257
They shimmer like the surface of water.

1154
01:42:45,859 --> 01:42:49,229
I feel as if I've seen this color before.

1155
01:42:51,265 --> 01:42:53,333
Sometime, long, long ago.

1156
01:42:54,568 --> 01:42:58,172
Somewhere.

1157
01:43:01,275 --> 01:43:02,676
What is this?

1158
01:43:04,645 --> 01:43:07,514
I felt something running down on my face.

1159
01:43:07,848 --> 01:43:09,750
(Sniffling)

1160
01:43:12,553 --> 01:43:13,887
Tears.

1161
01:43:16,490 --> 01:43:18,525
Overflowing tears.

1162
01:43:22,429 --> 01:43:25,732
The image of me
desperately wiping away my tears

1163
01:43:25,832 --> 01:43:28,468
can be seen in the mirror in the room.

1164
01:43:29,369 --> 01:43:32,706
The moonlight
gently illuminates the piano keys.

1165
01:43:33,473 --> 01:43:35,976
The cat quietly approaches me.

1166
01:43:36,577 --> 01:43:42,216
Then it puts its nose
against mine as if to kiss me.

1167
01:43:43,817 --> 01:43:48,522
The cat silently goes out the window.

1168
01:43:50,691 --> 01:43:57,397
This was the last time I ever saw them.

1169
01:44:13,013 --> 01:44:18,018
｢Left-Right Confusion｣
♪You rested your chin on your right hand.

1170
01:44:18,018 --> 01:44:19,419
♪You rested your chin on your right hand.

1171
01:44:19,653 --> 01:44:24,291
♪I held a lukewarm mug with my left hand.

1172
01:44:25,626 --> 01:44:31,965
♪Your right eyebrow was slightly slated downward.

1173
01:44:32,266 --> 01:44:36,403
♪Morning rained down on us so much.

1174
01:44:37,904 --> 01:44:39,506
♪One is enough.

1175
01:44:39,606 --> 01:44:42,643
♪Just one peony flower that never falls.

1176
01:44:42,743 --> 01:44:44,811
♪Let it strike your heart

1177
01:44:44,911 --> 01:44:50,450
♪and make you so happy that you could
forget about your heart.

1178
01:44:50,550 --> 01:44:52,052
♪One is enough.

1179
01:44:52,352 --> 01:45:02,963
♪Through the confusing night without
knowing right from left,

1180
01:45:03,497 --> 01:45:09,469
♪I grope my way all alone in dead silence.

1181
01:45:09,569 --> 01:45:15,642
♪If only I could let you know a piece of that.

1182
01:45:16,443 --> 01:45:22,749
♪Your left eyebrow was slightly slated downward.

1183
01:45:22,849 --> 01:45:25,752
♪It's hard for me to recall.

1184
01:45:25,986 --> 01:45:28,922
♪It seems that I can't tell.

1185
01:45:29,022 --> 01:45:34,995
♪Your right hand held the novel that
you bought one day.

1186
01:45:35,395 --> 01:45:41,468
♪Or was it your left hand?

1187
01:45:41,568 --> 01:45:47,074
♪～

1188
01:45:47,441 --> 01:45:49,076
♪One is enough.

1189
01:45:49,376 --> 01:45:52,012
♪Just one piece of the sunlight in the night.

1190
01:45:52,112 --> 01:45:54,481
♪Strike your heart with such sentiment

1191
01:45:54,581 --> 01:45:59,820
♪that I could peek inside your heart.

1192
01:45:59,920 --> 01:46:01,488
♪One is enough

1193
01:46:01,588 --> 01:46:12,699
♪to show that you could grope your way
in a flurry of hail in summer

1194
01:46:12,799 --> 01:46:19,039
♪and that your eyes would never close.

1195
01:46:19,940 --> 01:46:31,818
♪～

1196
01:46:31,918 --> 01:46:39,626
♪I would peel off my heart from my body bit by bit

1197
01:46:39,726 --> 01:46:41,161
♪and hand it to you,

1198
01:46:41,461 --> 01:46:44,164
♪and you could have all of it, so—

1199
01:46:44,464 --> 01:46:47,434
♪Take the ruby out of my sword-hilt,

1200
01:46:47,801 --> 01:46:51,004
♪the sapphires out of my eyes.

1201
01:46:51,405 --> 01:46:57,010
♪Just leave the leaden heart by my side.

1202
01:46:59,980 --> 01:47:01,615
♪One is enough.

1203
01:47:01,715 --> 01:47:04,751
♪Just one peony flower that never falls.

1204
01:47:04,851 --> 01:47:06,920
♪Let it strike your heart

1205
01:47:07,020 --> 01:47:12,492
♪and make you so happy that you could forget
about the tears you shed.

1206
01:47:12,592 --> 01:47:14,161
♪A little is enough.

1207
01:47:14,461 --> 01:47:21,935
♪Just a little sunlight to
make the drizzle stop today.

1208
01:47:25,205 --> 01:47:26,840
♪A little is enough.

1209
01:47:26,940 --> 01:47:32,446
♪Let me leave a little part of
my shoeprint in your world.

1210
01:47:32,546 --> 01:47:37,784
♪Can you see? Your happiness could be

1211
01:47:37,884 --> 01:47:39,619
♪more than just one.

1212
01:47:39,719 --> 01:47:50,597
♪Through the confusing night without
knowing right from left,

1213
01:47:50,697 --> 01:47:56,570
♪you have a long way to grope from here.

1214
01:47:57,003 --> 01:48:03,076
♪I'm the only one who will never laugh about it.

1215
01:48:03,543 --> 01:48:09,516
♪If only I could let you know a piece of that.

1216
01:48:13,119 --> 01:48:19,626
♪No matter what I eat, everything is tasteless.

1217
01:48:19,726 --> 01:48:24,097
♪It feels like I've just lost my body.

1218
01:48:25,632 --> 01:48:31,972
♪Your heart and my heart

1219
01:48:32,072 --> 01:48:37,077
♪would be as one forever, I believed.

1220
01:48:47,153 --> 01:48:52,158
｢Spring Thief｣
♪～

1221
01:48:52,158 --> 01:49:17,951
♪～

1222
01:49:18,051 --> 01:49:24,958
♪Out of the elevated bridge,
I saw blue patches through clouds

1223
01:49:25,759 --> 01:49:32,132
♪During these warm days,
I've been just waiting for a wind to blow

1224
01:49:33,099 --> 01:49:36,069
♪Sitting in the shade of a tree

1225
01:49:36,937 --> 01:49:39,239
♪Something sticks to my cheek

1226
01:49:40,907 --> 01:49:45,745
♪Look up to see blossoms in bloom
and falling over me

1227
01:49:48,048 --> 01:49:51,985
♪Fluttering petals takes our breath away

1228
01:49:52,085 --> 01:49:55,855
♪Even blinking is a bother

1229
01:49:55,956 --> 01:50:00,026
♪Look, even today becomes the past tomorrow

1230
01:50:00,126 --> 01:50:03,263
♪Just wait for the wind

1231
01:50:03,363 --> 01:50:07,334
♪So now we're left speechless

1232
01:50:07,634 --> 01:50:11,137
♪Even saying goodbye is a bother

1233
01:50:11,237 --> 01:50:16,042
♪Just blossoms are fluttering down in sunlight

1234
01:50:16,142 --> 01:50:19,079
♪Now like spring confetti

1235
01:50:19,179 --> 01:50:34,794
♪～

1236
01:50:34,894 --> 01:50:37,263
♪The next day we're meeting up again

1237
01:50:38,865 --> 01:50:41,868
♪There're fewer people viewing blossoms

1238
01:50:42,369 --> 01:50:45,138
♪Spring scent is about to disappear

1239
01:50:46,306 --> 01:50:49,075
♪Seems like summer is coming again

1240
01:50:50,176 --> 01:50:57,117
♪Out of the elevated bridge,
I saw you at the end of the road

1241
01:50:57,884 --> 01:51:00,420
♪I wonder how much time is left

1242
01:51:01,921 --> 01:51:04,257
♪How much longer can I see spring?

1243
01:51:05,291 --> 01:51:07,994
♪On a riverside hill,

1244
01:51:09,162 --> 01:51:11,998
♪sitting in the shade of a tree

1245
01:51:12,999 --> 01:51:20,807
♪Bloosoms are in bloom today just like yesterday

1246
01:51:20,907 --> 01:51:24,210
♪Let them take our breath away

1247
01:51:24,310 --> 01:51:27,881
♪Even blinking is a bother

1248
01:51:27,981 --> 01:51:32,052
♪This storm blowing off the blossoms is

1249
01:51:32,152 --> 01:51:35,321
♪Literally a spring thief

1250
01:51:35,722 --> 01:51:39,793
♪The wind makes the time fly again today

1251
01:51:39,893 --> 01:51:43,363
♪Even standing up is a bother

1252
01:51:43,463 --> 01:51:48,134
♪Blue sky shows through the blossoms, fluttering

1253
01:51:48,234 --> 01:51:51,104
♪Still like spring confetti

1254
01:51:51,204 --> 01:52:06,886
♪～

1255
01:52:06,986 --> 01:52:09,355
♪Going to see you again today

1256
01:52:10,490 --> 01:52:13,159
♪And sit in the shade of a tree

1257
01:52:14,327 --> 01:52:16,930
♪I let out a sigh

1258
01:52:18,264 --> 01:52:20,967
♪Blossoms will be gone soon

1259
01:52:22,302 --> 01:52:24,771
♪Going to see you again tomorrow

1260
01:52:25,972 --> 01:52:28,842
♪Spring will soon be over

1261
01:52:29,843 --> 01:52:34,948
♪As if with reluctance, time flutters down

1262
01:52:37,917 --> 01:52:41,020
♪When I sing love, I fall short of words

1263
01:52:41,121 --> 01:52:44,524
♪Even rhyming is a bother

1264
01:52:44,824 --> 01:52:52,332
♪To this season in bloom,
I doubt words can ever do justice

1265
01:52:52,432 --> 01:52:56,336
♪Fluttering petals leaves us speechless

1266
01:52:56,436 --> 01:53:00,206
♪Even blinking is a bother

1267
01:53:00,306 --> 01:53:03,810
♪Nobody but us are here for the blossoms

1268
01:53:04,144 --> 01:53:07,881
♪Don't go just yet, spring confetti

1269
01:53:07,981 --> 01:53:11,484
♪For just a little longer

1270
01:53:11,785 --> 01:53:15,255
♪Only a few are left

1271
01:53:23,463 --> 01:53:26,966
♪Just two more flowers

1272
01:53:31,070 --> 01:53:34,407
♪Just one more to go

1273
01:53:38,578 --> 01:53:43,383
♪Only the leaves are left behind, fluttering

1274
01:53:43,483 --> 01:53:46,486
♪Now, spring is over

1275
01:53:56,996 --> 01:54:02,001
｢Algernon｣
♪～

1276
01:54:02,001 --> 01:54:34,367
♪～

1277
01:54:37,237 --> 01:55:29,555
♪～

1278
01:55:30,356 --> 01:55:36,930
♪I wonder why you gave me a heart.

1279
01:55:37,030 --> 01:55:42,702
♪Why did you draw eyes on my face?

1280
01:55:43,569 --> 01:55:50,310
♪Bigger than the sky,
swallowing the wind that carried the clouds,

1281
01:55:50,410 --> 01:55:56,115
♪my eyes were dreaming once again.

1282
01:55:58,017 --> 01:56:03,056
♪With bare feet,

1283
01:56:07,226 --> 01:56:13,700
♪you're changing slowly, only a little,

1284
01:56:14,000 --> 01:56:20,406
♪like watching a bread puff up little by little.

1285
01:56:20,506 --> 01:56:24,577
♪You keep on running slowly,

1286
01:56:24,677 --> 01:56:33,987
♪unafraid of what lies beyond the long maze.

1287
01:56:35,388 --> 01:56:41,728
♪I wonder why you gave me a name.

1288
01:56:42,161 --> 01:56:47,633
♪Why did you make hands for me?

1289
01:56:48,735 --> 01:56:55,141
♪Bigger than the ocean,
swallowing the wave that carried the sand,

1290
01:56:55,341 --> 01:57:01,080
♪my small hands were still gazing into the distance.

1291
01:57:01,214 --> 01:57:06,352
♪With a yawn,

1292
01:57:10,490 --> 01:57:14,594
♪we're falling asleep slowly,

1293
01:57:14,694 --> 01:57:17,130
♪for a long time to come,

1294
01:57:17,230 --> 01:57:23,736
♪walking slowly by the base of a big tree

1295
01:57:24,037 --> 01:57:28,107
♪that grows in the center of our heads

1296
01:57:28,207 --> 01:57:37,250
♪to be unafraid of what lies beyond the long maze.

1297
01:57:37,483 --> 01:57:43,423
♪Someday, will we meet the one
we can never catch up with?

1298
01:57:44,323 --> 01:57:50,163
♪Someday, will we flinch at a wall
that we can never clear?

1299
01:57:50,830 --> 01:57:56,736
♪Someday, will you give up on it too?

1300
01:57:58,271 --> 01:58:01,340
♪Slowly changing.

1301
01:58:01,441 --> 01:58:04,677
♪Slowly changing.

1302
01:58:04,777 --> 01:58:07,213
♪Slowly changing.

1303
01:58:07,313 --> 01:58:11,417
♪We're losing memories slowly,

1304
01:58:11,517 --> 01:58:13,719
♪only a little,

1305
01:58:13,820 --> 01:58:20,460
♪like watching a tower collapse little by little.

1306
01:58:20,560 --> 01:58:24,664
♪We're falling asleep slowly,

1307
01:58:24,764 --> 01:58:28,134
♪falling asleep slowly.

1308
01:58:30,570 --> 01:58:37,243
♪You're changing slowly, only a little,

1309
01:58:37,343 --> 01:58:43,749
♪like the shade growing in the center of that tree.

1310
01:58:43,850 --> 01:58:47,887
♪You keep on running slowly,

1311
01:58:48,187 --> 01:58:57,196
♪unafraid of what lies beyond the long maze,

1312
01:58:57,763 --> 01:59:04,437
♪losing your way sometimes, for sure.

1313
01:59:04,537 --> 02:00:44,637
♪～

1314
02:01:14,900 --> 02:01:17,403
This is a series of pictures

1315
02:01:17,503 --> 02:01:20,840
of mysterious animals
that visted my home.

1316
02:01:21,007 --> 02:01:24,744
After midnight,
they would sit near my piano

1317
02:01:24,844 --> 02:01:26,912
and dance strange dances.

1318
02:01:27,013 --> 02:01:30,750
There was a mysterious charm to them.

1319
02:01:31,050 --> 02:01:35,354
They inspired me to create
this series of ten paintings.

1320
02:01:35,454 --> 02:01:38,691
I certainly hope that you enjoy them.

1321
02:01:42,762 --> 02:01:45,998
It was time for my exhibition.

1322
02:01:46,365 --> 02:01:48,801
I have a small sheet of paper in my hands.

1323
02:01:48,934 --> 02:01:52,872
It's a small postcard-size sheet
outlining the solo exhibition.

1324
02:01:52,972 --> 02:01:56,409
There were a few people
inside the small exhibition space

1325
02:01:56,509 --> 02:01:58,644
in a renovated room of a building.

1326
02:01:58,744 --> 02:02:02,515
Still, I feel
a strange sense of satisfaction.

1327
02:02:04,050 --> 02:02:05,484
Hello.

1328
02:02:05,584 --> 02:02:08,321
Well, if it isn't my landlord.

1329
02:02:08,421 --> 02:02:11,757
I see you've come. Thank you.

1330
02:02:11,857 --> 02:02:14,627
Please, enjoy.

1331
02:02:15,461 --> 02:02:17,363
(Woman) May I have one?

1332
02:02:17,763 --> 02:02:19,665
I hear a voice.

1333
02:02:20,566 --> 02:02:22,968
I see a once familiar face.

1334
02:02:23,569 --> 02:02:27,940
She's the girlfriend
I broke up with a while back.

1335
02:02:29,608 --> 02:02:35,448
Nice to see you. I appreciate
all your help with this.

1336
02:02:35,548 --> 02:02:36,716
(Ex-girlfriend) No problem.

1337
02:02:36,816 --> 02:02:40,686
The pictures are good.
I just wanted to lend you a hand.

1338
02:02:41,721 --> 02:02:44,757
You seem pretty busy lately.

1339
02:02:44,857 --> 02:02:45,891
(Ex-girlfriend) Yes.

1340
02:02:45,991 --> 02:02:50,096
Since I plan exhibitions while working,
I don't have much time.

1341
02:02:50,396 --> 02:02:53,899
But I enjoy it. It's what I want to do.

1342
02:02:54,133 --> 02:02:58,704
I stop myself before saying,
」You haven't changed.」

1343
02:02:59,472 --> 02:03:03,609
People seem as if they haven't changed,
but everyone changes.

1344
02:03:03,709 --> 02:03:06,579
Time doesn't pass only for me.

1345
02:03:06,946 --> 02:03:12,551
She looks at the paper in her left
hand,while my eyes are glued

1346
02:03:12,818 --> 02:03:15,154
to the ring on her ring finger.

1347
02:03:16,622 --> 02:03:20,993
Well, anyway... Enjoy.

1348
02:03:21,093 --> 02:03:25,998
(Ex-girlfriend) Yes. I'm hoping
this will be a good exhibition for you.

1349
02:03:28,801 --> 02:03:31,971
There's nothing special
I can say about the exhibition.

1350
02:03:32,071 --> 02:03:36,542
It lasted for a few weeks
and ended without incident.

1351
02:03:36,642 --> 02:03:40,980
One big development was that offers
were made on some of the paintings.

1352
02:03:41,080 --> 02:03:47,086
After much deliberation,
I kept the cat picture, and sold the rest.

1353
02:03:51,056 --> 02:03:52,591
(Ex-girlfriend) Nice work.

1354
02:03:52,858 --> 02:03:54,727
Oh, thank you.

1355
02:03:54,827 --> 02:03:57,430
(Ex-girlfriend) How was the exhibition?

1356
02:03:57,630 --> 02:03:58,764
It was great.

1357
02:03:58,864 --> 02:04:02,034
It's good to hear people's
reactions in person.

1358
02:04:02,134 --> 02:04:04,437
And I think I made some connections.

1359
02:04:04,537 --> 02:04:07,706
But best of all,
I got a job offer to paint.

1360
02:04:07,807 --> 02:04:10,209
After seeing this, they wanted to work with me.

1361
02:04:10,509 --> 02:04:11,444
(Ex-girlfriend) Really?

1362
02:04:11,544 --> 02:04:13,612
And I sold several paintings.

1363
02:04:13,712 --> 02:04:16,048
Not just of the dancing animals,

1364
02:04:16,148 --> 02:04:18,617
but some of my old paintings too.

1365
02:04:18,717 --> 02:04:20,152
(Ex-girlfriend) That's fantastic!

1366
02:04:20,453 --> 02:04:22,121
I told you about them before.

1367
02:04:22,221 --> 02:04:25,825
They're based on dreams of scenes
from a previous life.

1368
02:04:25,925 --> 02:04:28,761
Remember? You said you didn't like them.

1369
02:04:28,861 --> 02:04:30,062
(Ex-girlfriend) I remember those.

1370
02:04:30,162 --> 02:04:33,833
But that's not what I meant
when I said that.

1371
02:04:33,933 --> 02:04:37,203
I never said that I didn't like them.

1372
02:04:37,903 --> 02:04:38,838
Huh?

1373
02:04:38,938 --> 02:04:41,140
(Ex-girlfriend)
I just said they were dull.

1374
02:04:41,240 --> 02:04:44,677
I said, for a picture to be
accessible to people,

1375
02:04:44,777 --> 02:04:48,047
it's better if there's something
interesting about it.

1376
02:04:48,147 --> 02:04:52,952
Being dull doesn't affect
the quality of the painting.

1377
02:04:53,052 --> 02:04:55,588
Even if the setting's commonplace,

1378
02:04:55,688 --> 02:04:59,124
the painting will still have its own
unique value.

1379
02:04:59,225 --> 02:05:03,028
Even paintings
nobody buys are great paintings.

1380
02:05:06,565 --> 02:05:10,536
Come to think of it, she's probably right.

1381
02:05:11,770 --> 02:05:14,273
Painting is my livelihood,

1382
02:05:14,707 --> 02:05:18,644
so she was just giving me some
helpful advice.

1383
02:05:18,844 --> 02:05:22,047
She wasn't judging me.

1384
02:05:23,082 --> 02:05:25,918
What was it that possessed me?

1385
02:05:27,620 --> 02:05:31,957
That's a great thought.
Who said it? It really encouraged me.

1386
02:05:32,057 --> 02:05:33,926
(Ex-girlfriend) You said it.

1387
02:05:34,727 --> 02:05:37,663
Have you forgotten what you once said?

1388
02:05:39,298 --> 02:05:41,300
You haven't changed a bit.

1389
02:05:44,236 --> 02:05:46,639
I'm at a loss for words.

1390
02:05:47,573 --> 02:05:50,276
Bathed in the evening light
streaming in through the window,

1391
02:05:50,576 --> 02:05:53,112
she laughs mischievously.

1392
02:05:54,079 --> 02:05:58,117
The ring on her ring finger sparkles.

1393
02:06:02,555 --> 02:06:04,657
(Ex-girlfriend)
We'll say bye here. Thank you.

1394
02:06:04,757 --> 02:06:07,893
Okay. I've got to get back
to clean up anyway.

1395
02:06:07,993 --> 02:06:08,994
(Ex-girlfriend)
Hang in there.

1396
02:06:09,094 --> 02:06:11,630
I'll send you the final paperwork later.

1397
02:06:11,730 --> 02:06:12,765
Okay.

1398
02:06:12,865 --> 02:06:15,734
(Ex-girlfriend)
So, are you glad you did it?

1399
02:06:18,737 --> 02:06:20,172
It really feels like

1400
02:06:20,706 --> 02:06:23,976
these are my first
interesting paintings in a while.

1401
02:06:24,276 --> 02:06:28,747
I've gotten work too.
My future seems bright.

1402
02:06:29,715 --> 02:06:33,919
It's all thanks to those animals.

1403
02:06:34,653 --> 02:06:38,157
(Ex-girlfriend) You're so deadpan,
I can't tell when you're kidding.

1404
02:06:38,257 --> 02:06:40,593
Oh, sorry.

1405
02:06:40,693 --> 02:06:42,962
(Ex-girlfriend) I think it's
a great concept though.

1406
02:06:43,062 --> 02:06:45,631
Animals are cute and accessible.

1407
02:06:45,731 --> 02:06:49,268
The paintings had a coherent theme
and were easy on the eyes.

1408
02:06:49,368 --> 02:06:52,705
And it was quite amusing, too.

1409
02:06:52,805 --> 02:06:53,806
What was?

1410
02:06:53,906 --> 02:06:57,743
(Ex-girlfriend) Those animals
kind of resemble you.

1411
02:06:57,843 --> 02:07:00,879
Really?
Do I look that much like an animal?

1412
02:07:00,980 --> 02:07:06,685
How can I phrase it? Your expressions,
your mannerisms. Your aura.

1413
02:07:07,186 --> 02:07:09,722
Like that cat.

1414
02:07:09,822 --> 02:07:12,791
It looks just like you
when you play the piano.

1415
02:07:13,325 --> 02:07:18,797
Eyes closed, looking upward
with your nose poking into the air.

1416
02:07:22,234 --> 02:07:23,836
The piano?

1417
02:07:24,870 --> 02:07:27,206
(Ex-girlfriend) Yes. The piano.

1418
02:07:48,227 --> 02:07:50,829
Dancing animals...

1419
02:07:54,166 --> 02:07:57,136
This is a series of paintings

1420
02:07:57,870 --> 02:08:02,007
of mysterious animals
that visted my home.

1421
02:08:03,175 --> 02:08:08,414
After midnight,
they would sit near my piano

1422
02:08:09,014 --> 02:08:12,084
and dance a strange dance.

1423
02:08:15,854 --> 02:08:17,990
A strange dance...

1424
02:08:24,763 --> 02:08:27,099
A strange dance...

1425
02:08:35,908 --> 02:08:39,778
A strange dance...

1426
02:08:42,481 --> 02:08:46,418
It looks just like you
when you play the piano...

1427
02:08:56,395 --> 02:08:58,731
(Piano plays)

1428
02:09:06,972 --> 02:09:10,509
No, maybe it's the other way around.

1429
02:09:11,510 --> 02:09:13,912
Was I mistaken?

1430
02:09:15,013 --> 02:09:18,484
They weren't dancing.

1431
02:09:19,451 --> 02:09:24,957
Maybe they wanted to play the piano...

1432
02:09:25,424 --> 02:09:36,835
♪～(Piano Sonata 」Moonlight」)

1433
02:09:36,935 --> 02:09:39,204
I stand before the piano.

1434
02:09:39,805 --> 02:09:42,808
Moonlight illuminates the piano keys.

1435
02:09:43,108 --> 02:09:47,112
As I look at myself in the mirror
out of the side of my eye,

1436
02:09:47,246 --> 02:09:50,315
I slowly lower my arms to play.

1437
02:09:51,450 --> 02:09:54,219
That melody I have played many times,

1438
02:09:54,787 --> 02:09:58,957
Beethoven's Piano Sonata No. 14.

1439
02:10:00,159 --> 02:10:02,828
I see myself in the mirror.

1440
02:10:03,362 --> 02:10:06,999
My body moves as I play the piano keys.

1441
02:10:07,299 --> 02:10:13,806
And it looks as if I'm dancing
a strange dance.

1442
02:10:15,307 --> 02:11:16,435
♪～

1443
02:11:23,141 --> 02:15:00,826
♪～

